57.1	Scott_McCloud	Scott McCloud	Scott McCloud (born Scott McLeod on June 10, 1960) is an American cartoonist and theorist on comics as a distinct literary and artistic medium. He is most notable for his non-fiction books about comics, Understanding Comics, Reinventing Comics and Making Comics, for which he has been called the "Marshall McLuhan of comics".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Scott_McCloud.Making_Comics_Tour.RISD.gk.JPG/230px-Scott_McCloud.Making_Comics_Tour.RISD.gk.JPG
